# Fraud Risk Prioritization & Operational Analytics  
**Animesh Choubey** | MSBA, Cal State East Bay · [GitHub](https://github.com/animesh-501)

---

## Executive Summary

Built an end-to-end fraud risk scoring system that prioritizes analyst review queues using cost-sensitive modeling and graph-based fraud ring detection.  
Goal: **catch meaningful fraud while keeping analyst workload manageable.**

---

## Business Problem

A payment platform processing **50K+ transactions/month** needed a way to:

- Identify the highest-risk transactions first
- Avoid overwhelming analysts with false positives
- Understand **why** transactions were flagged
- Translate model performance into **operational ROI**

---

## What I Built

- Gradient boosting fraud risk model (LightGBM)
- Entity graph connecting cards, devices, and email domains
- Fraud ring detection using network features
- Plain-language explanation outputs for each flagged transaction
- SQL workflows for operational monitoring and review queues
- Cost model to determine the **optimal decision threshold**

---

## Key Outcomes

| Metric | Result |
|--------|--------|
| PR-AUC | 0.27 → **0.40** (+53% vs baseline) |
| Precision @ 2% review rate | **53%** (target: 25%) |
| Recall @ operating threshold | **~58%** of fraud captured |
| Monthly impact (50K txns) | **~$200K fraud prevented** vs ~$40K review cost |
| Transactions explained | **118,108** with plain-language reasoning |

